20see%20a%20few%20of%20these%20pop%20up%20in%20my%20feed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20last%20week%2C%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-job-cuts-everything-we-know-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%20culled%20some%204%2C000%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20expected%20total%20silence.%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20had%20announced%20that%20the%20cuts%20were%20designed%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-performance-cuts-mark-zuckerberg-memo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elow%20performers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20burdening%20the%20departing%20employees%20with%20the%20professional%20equivalent%20of%20a%20scarlet%20letter.%20I%20felt%20terrible%20for%20them.%20No%20one%2C%20I%20thought%2C%20would%20want%20to%20call%20attention%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20they'd%20been%20branded%20as%20below%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoy%2C%20was%20I%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20day%2C%20laid-off%20Meta%20employees%20were%20taking%20to%20LinkedIn%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20to%20announce%20they%20were%20looking%20for%20work%2C%20but%20to%20fight%20back%20against%20Zuckerberg's%20assessment%20of%20their%20work.%20It%20was%20a%20new%20iteration%20of%20the%20classic%20%23opentowork%20post%2C%20ditching%20the%20deference%20for%20a%20tone%20of%20defiance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20not%20a%20low%20performer%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20content%20manager%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20an%20adaptive%20hard%20worker%20who%20thrives%20in%20work%20that%20I%20can%20be%20passionate%20about.%26quot%3B%20A%20product%20designer%20asserted%3A%20%26quot%3BThat%20label%20is%20misleading%2C%20and%20for%20many%20of%20us%2C%20it's%20flat-out%20wrong.%26quot%3B%20A%20lawyer%20%E2%80%94%20deriding%20what%20she%20called%20%26quot%3BZuck's%20newfound%20'masculine%20energy'%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20offered%20to%20provide%20the%20receipts%3A%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20a%20'low%20performer.'%20I've%20got%20the%20reviews%20to%20prove%20it%2C%20and%20countless%20colleagues%20and%20managers%20will%20vouch%20for%20me!%26quot%3B%20A%20data%20scientist%20even%20uploaded%20screenshots%20of%20his%20glowing%20performance%20reviews%2C%20which%20indicated%20he%20routinely%20%26quot%3Bexceeded%20expectations%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bgreatly%20exceeded%20expectations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20something%20we%20haven't%20seen%20before%20in%20the%20professional%20world%3A%20Employees%20sticking%20up%20for%20themselves%20in%20public%2C%20and%20calling%20out%20their%20former%20employer%20for%20misrepresenting%20their%20work.%20When%20LinkedIn%20introduced%20the%20%23opentowork%20feature%20during%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20it%20was%20a%20tall%20order%20to%20get%20people%20to%20announce%20that%20they'd%20been%20laid%20off.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20people%20usually%20kept%20their%20dismissal%20private%2C%20fearing%20the%20stigma%20would%20prevent%20them%20from%20getting%20another%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20began%20to%20change%20in%20late%202022%2C%20when%20a%20huge%20round%20of%20layoffs%20hit%20the%20tech%20sector.%20Suddenly%2C%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20coders%2C%20product%20managers%2C%20and%20marketers%20found%20themselves%20out%20of%20a%20job%20all%20at%20once.%20Some%20of%20their%20CEOs%20went%20out%20of%20their%20way%20to%20apologize%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-memo-mark-zuckerberg-employees-mass-layoffs-job-cuts-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoverhiring%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20to%20praise%20their%20axed%20staffers%20as%20great%20employees.%20That%20encouraged%20people%20to%20use%20the%20%23opentowork%20banner%20to%20announce%20that%20they'd%20been%20laid%20off.%20Last%20summer%2C%20when%20I%20spoke%20with%20corporate%20recruiters%20about%20the%20trend%2C%20most%20told%20me%20it%20no%20longer%20gave%20them%20pause%20to%20see%20that%20a%20candidate%20had%20been%20laid%20off.%20They'd%20come%20to%20understand%20that%20it%20doesn't%20automatically%20cast%20doubt%20on%20someone's%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Meta's%20employees%20are%20taking%20that%20realization%20to%20the%20next%20level.%20The%20groundswell%20of%20defiance%20started%20last%20year%2C%20when%20a%20handful%20of%20people%20posted%20videos%20of%20themselves%20on%20TikTok%20as%20they%20received%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-firings-tech-hr-tiktok-cloudflare-employee-morale-bad-business-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enews%20of%20their%20layoffs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20most%20viral%20was%20Brittany%20Pietsch%2C%20a%20Cloudflare%20employee%20who%20kept%20asking%20the%20HR%20person%20for%20evidence%20of%20her%20supposed%20low%20performance.%20The%20videos%20were%20uncomfortable%2C%20but%20I%20found%20it%20refreshing%20to%20watch%20these%20young%20people%20tell%20%3Cem%3Etheir%20%3C%2Fem%3Eside%20of%20the%20story.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20new%20crop%20of%20%23opentowork%20posts%20is%20enabling%20Meta's%20employees%20to%20assert%20their%20value%20in%20the%20marketplace%20%E2%80%94%20using%20social%20media%2C%20the%20very%20thing%20Zuckerberg%20helped%20supercharge%2C%20to%20counter%20the%20narrative%20he's%20telling%20about%20the%20layoffs.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20we%20can't%20do%20anything%20about%20being%20laid%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Meta%20research%20manager%20posted%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20aren't%20without%20any%20agency.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20is%3A%20Will%20standing%20up%20to%20your%20former%20boss%20hurt%20your%20chances%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffind-job-searching-hunt-tips-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elanding%20a%20new%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20The%20standard%20advice%20for%20laid-off%20workers%20is%20to%20avoid%20saying%20anything%20negative%20about%20their%20former%20employers%2C%20both%20on%20social%20media%20and%20in%20job%20interviews.%20Ashley%20Herd%2C%20a%20former%20head%20of%20HR%20who%20founded%20a%20firm%20that%20provides%20training%20for%20managers%2C%20acknowledges%20that%20speaking%20up%20might%20turn%20off%20some%20potential%20employers.%20But%20getting%20rejected%20by%20them%2C%20she%20adds%2C%20might%20not%20be%20a%20bad%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGood%20employers%20are%20looking%20for%20people%20who%20are%20good%20communicators%20%E2%80%94%20who%20can%20advocate%20for%20themselves%20just%20like%20they%20would%20in%20their%20role%20for%20the%20organization%2C%26quot%3B%20Herd%20says.%20%26quot%3BThose%20that%20speak%20up%20might%20realistically%20find%20themselves%20with%20a%20smaller%20pool%20of%20potential%20employers%2C%20but%20that%20will%20be%20a%20group%20that%20actually%20aligns%20with%20their%20values%20and%20supports%20long-term%20career%20success%20and%20happiness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESandra%20Sucher%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20who%20studies%20layoffs%2C%20agrees%20that%20it's%20good%20for%20employees%20to%20stick%20up%20for%20themselves.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20it's%20a%20mistake%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BAs%20soon%20as%20you've%20got%20the%20CEO%20of%20my%20company%20saying%2C%20'I'm%20laying%20off%20people%20because%20they're%20no%20good%20at%20their%20job%2C'%20reasonable%20people%20are%20going%20to%20say%2C%20'Do%20I%20accept%20that%20or%20do%20I%20try%20to%20change%20the%20narrative%20here%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that's%20their%20goal%2C%20Meta's%20employees%20seem%20to%20be%20succeeding.%20People%20have%20begun%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-surprise-employees-strong-performers-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equestion%20the%20%26quot%3Blow%20performer%26quot%3B%20label%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Zuckerberg%20has%20been%20throwing%20around.%20When%20those%20who%20were%20laid%20off%20start%20sending%20out%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%2C%20recruiters%20will%20likely%20have%20heard%20that%20the%20purge%20included%20a%20lot%20of%20employees%20with%20excellent%20performance%20reviews.%20Besides%2C%20the%20defiant%20posts%20are%20proving%20to%20be%20a%20good%20way%20to%20kick%20off%20a%20job%20search%3A%20Many%20of%20the%20comments%20on%20LinkedIn%20are%20filled%20with%20warm%20endorsements%20from%20ex-colleagues%20and%20networking%20offers%20from%20total%20strangers.%20This%2C%20ironically%2C%20was%20always%20the%20power%20of%20social%20media%2C%20as%20Zuckerberg%20championed%20it%20%E2%80%94%20the%20promise%20of%20%26quot%3Bconnecting%20people%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bbuilding%20community.%26quot%3B%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20making%20good%20on%20the%20company's%20slogans%2C%20Meta's%20former%20employees%20have%20proven%20themselves%20to%20be%20high%20performers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faki-ito%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAki%20Ito%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20chief%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-low-performers-zuckerberg-linkedin-job-searching-social-media-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739869502000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67afa0b07bb3f854015cfd09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-low-performers-zuckerberg-linkedin-job-searching-social-media-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mark%20Zuckerberg%20dissed%20their%20work%2C%20saying%20they%20were%20laid%20off%20from%20Meta%20for%20underperforming.%20Now%20they're%20clapping%20back.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aito%40businessinsider.com%20(Aki%20Ito)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-low-performers-zuckerberg-linkedin-job-searching-social-media-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22WFH%20has%20made%20everyone%20NSFW%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20working%20on%20their%20laptops%20in%20various%20positions%3A%20laying%20on%20couches%2C%20sitting%20in%20chairs%2C%20laying%20on%20the%20bed%2C%20laying%20in%20the%20bathtub%20and%20doing%20the%20splits%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67acb8c4eb4be2fff9a46262%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%C2%A0%3Cp%3EDmytro%20Betsenko%2FGetty%2C%20visualspace%2FGetty%2C%20Westend61%2FGetty%2C%20Jetta%20Productions%20Inc%2FGetty%2C%20PM%20Images%2FGetty%2C%20tirc83%2FGetty%2C%20svetikd%2FGetty%2C%20Ava%20Horton%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-work-from-home-benefits-as-good-as-raise-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperks%20of%20working%20from%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20the%20skipped%20commute%2C%20the%20chance%20of%20a%20quick%20midday%20workout%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20formal%20workwear.%20Many%20people%20say%20it%20makes%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhybrid-work-from-home-office-culture-remote-jobs-productivity-happiness-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20productive%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20at%20least%20just%20as%20productive%20as%20when%20they're%20in%20the%20office.%20But%20there%20are%20also%20some%20drawbacks%20when%20your%20office%20becomes%20your%20couch.%20Among%20them%3A%20You%20can%20get%20a%20little%20weird.%20A%20lot%20of%20alone%20time%20can%20result%20in%20some%20lost%20muscle%20memory%2C%20socialization-wise%2C%20and%20some%20slightly%20freaky%20habits%20you'd%20probably%20keep%20under%20wraps%20if%20other%20human%20beings%20were%20in%20eyeshot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnouska%20Shenn%2C%20who%20runs%20a%20workplace%20wellness%20agency%20in%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20undertakes%20long%2C%20involved%20beauty%20treatments%20on%20days%20she's%20working%20from%20home%20and%20doesn't%20have%20meetings.%20She%20does%20a%20lighter%20version%20of%20the%20scary-looking%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.glamour.com%2Fstory%2Fmorning-shed-tiktok-trend%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emorning%20shed%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20trend%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeauty-trend-predictions-2025-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epopularized%20on%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20between%20sending%20emails%2C%20she%20applies%20and%20removes%20a%20combination%20of%20face%20masks%2C%20wrinkle%20patches%2C%20hair%20curlers%2C%20and%20more%20that%20is%20very%20much%20not%20other-people%20appropriate.%20The%20getup%20is%20tough%20to%20sleep%20in%2C%20so%20she%20takes%20advantage%20of%20the%20ability%20to%20do%20the%20routine%20during%20the%20day.%20Plus%2C%20it's%20not%20something%20she%20really%20wants%20her%20partner%20to%20witness%20%E2%80%94%20you%20know%2C%20to%20keep%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20the%20mystery%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20guess%20it's%20quite%20a%20luxury%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Shenn%2C%20who's%20been%20working%20from%20home%20since%20starting%20her%20business%2C%20The%20Yoga%20Company%2C%20in%202017.%20She's%20never%20been%20caught%20masked%20up%20in%20a%20spur-of-the-moment%20meeting%2C%20though%20if%20she%20were%2C%20she'd%20take%20it%20off.%20%26quot%3BTruthfully%2C%20I%20was%20one%20of%20those%20weirdos%20at%20the%20office%20who%20used%20to%20sit%20on%20a%20big%20exercise%20ball%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bso%20maybe%20these%20habits%20aren't%20such%20a%20non%20sequitur%2C%20but%20I've%20certainly%20become%20more%20shameless%20since%20I%20began%20working%20from%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20five%20years%20into%20the%20vast%20pandemic-driven%20remote-work%20experiment%20%E2%80%94%20and%20about%20three%20years%20into%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-requiring-return-to-office-rto-mandate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn-to-office%20battle%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20employers%20and%20employees.%20While%20people%20aren't%20working%20remotely%20as%20much%20as%20they%20were%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20when%20nearly%20two-thirds%20of%20work%20was%20being%20done%20at%20home%2C%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20work%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-hybrid-jobs-rto-jpmorgan-amazon-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estill%20happening%20beyond%20the%20confines%20of%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20time%20can%20get%20strange%20%E2%80%94%20and%20make%20the%20in-office%20time%20a%20little%20awkward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENick%20Bloom%2C%20a%20Stanford%20economist%20who%20focuses%20on%20remote%20work%2C%20has%20found%20that%20employees%20who%20work%20from%20home%20save%20about%2010%20minutes%20a%20day%20on%20grooming.%20It%20can%20be%20nice%20to%20skip%20a%20shave%20or%20go%20makeup-free%2C%20which%20remote%20workers%20do%20at%20higher%20rates%20than%20those%20in%20the%20office.%20But%20it%20can%20also%20be%20a%20little%20gross.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dropbox.com%2Fscl%2Ffi%2Fm0d5rtg202t78ajg91vij%2FAEA_Jan2025.pdf%3Frlkey%3Dvyw029x5by0haq867l529b3fa%26e%3D1%26dl%3D0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20of%20Bloom's%20recent%20surveys%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2073%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20showered%20before%20working%20from%20home%2C%20compared%20with%2085%25%20who%20said%20they%20showered%20before%20going%20into%20the%20office.%20Eighty-one%20percent%20of%20remote%20workers%20said%20they%20put%20on%20deodorant%2C%20compared%20with%2095%25%20of%20in-office%20workers.%20For%20toothbrushing%2C%20the%20margin%20was%20slimmer%3A%2092%25%20versus%2095%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20of%20this%20is%20understandable%2C%20but%20some%20of%20it%20%E2%80%94%20like%20brushing%20teeth%20%E2%80%94%20I%20thought%20was%20about%20oral%20hygiene%20not%20going%20into%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Bloom%20said%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEric%20Mochnacz%2C%20who%20works%20for%20an%20HR%20consultancy%20based%20in%20New%20York%2C%20has%20developed%20what%20he%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bunique%20routine%26quot%3B%20while%20working%20from%20home%20that%2C%20if%20anything%2C%20sounds%20more%20over-the-top%20than%20underachieving.%20He%20gets%20up%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%20early%20to%20play%20New%20York%20Times%20games%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-times-editor-wordle-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWordle%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20read%20on%20the%20couch.%20Between%20calls%2C%20he%20does%20chores%3A%20washing%20dishes%2C%20dropping%20off%20the%20rent%20check%2C%20going%20grocery%20shopping.%20He%20considers%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bclarity%20break%2C%26quot%3B%20part%20of%20stress%20relief.%20Also%20among%20his%20at-home%20stress%20relievers%20is%20song-and-dance%20time%20that%20is%20a%20no-go%20on%20days%20he's%20in%20the%20office.%20%26quot%3BI'll%20just%20put%20a%20Spotify%20song%20and%20dance%20around%20my%20apartment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20Lately%20he's%20been%20on%20a%20Taylor%20Swift%20kick.%20He%20thinks%20the%20setup%20makes%20him%20more%20productive%20in%20work%20and%20in%20life%20%E2%80%94%20the%20built-in%20time-outs%20help%20him%20do%20his%20job%20better%2C%20and%20he%20keeps%20his%20Peloton%20streak%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMochnacz's%20company%20has%20a%20hybrid%20setup%2C%20and%20he's%20noticed%20that%20work-from-home%20weirdness%20translates%20to%20some%20weirdness%20in%20the%20office%2C%20in%20that%20he%20can%20be%20a%20little%20extra%20chatty.%20Whether%20it's%20a%20%26quot%3Bbrain%20fart%26quot%3B%20about%20some%20work%20stuff%20or%20Matthew%20Lillard's%20potential%20return%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscream-7-jenna-ortega-melissa-barrera-controversy-explained-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BScream%26quot%3B%20franchise%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20feels%20compelled%20to%20gush%20to%20a%20colleague.%20%26quot%3BI'm%2C%20like%2C%20hoping%20people%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliam%20Chopik%2C%20a%20social-personality%20psychologist%20at%20Michigan%20State%20University%20who%20studies%20relationships%2C%20says%20that%20while%20working%20from%20home%20gives%20people%20a%20%26quot%3Bton%20of%20flexibility%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20can%20also%20affect%20their%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20something%20to%20say%20about%20being%20around%20other%20people%20that%20kind%20of%20polices%20our%20behavior%20a%20little%20bit%2C%20or%20at%20least%20makes%20us%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20vigilant%20to%20stuff%20that%20we%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20might%20be%20a%20little%20less%20likely%20to%20get%20distracted.%20You%20probably%20don't%20talk%20to%20yourself%2C%20you%20don't%20say%20weird%20things%2C%20you%20don't%20randomly%20start%20singing.%20I%20do%20all%20those%20things%20at%20home%2C%20and%20the%20truth%20is%20that%20I%20would%20die%20of%20cringe%20if%20I%20did%20that%20in%20front%20of%20other%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnline%2C%20there's%20plenty%20of%20chatter%20about%20the%20habits%20people%20have%20developed%20at%20home%20that%20aren't%20really%20appropriate%20for%20prime%20time%2C%20or%20work%20time.%20They%20don't%20change%20out%20of%20their%20pajamas%20(or%20they%20get%20day%20and%20night%20pajamas).%20They%20maybe%20start%20happy%20hour%20a%20little%20early%2C%20talk%20to%20themselves%2C%20or%20engage%20in%20levels%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fdoomscrolling%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoomscrolling%3C%2Fa%3E%20they'd%20get%20into%20trouble%20for%20if%20their%20manager%20saw.%20Some%20people%20say%20they%20feel%20like%20they%20never%20take%20a%20break%3B%20others%20say%20their%20short%20breaks%20turn%20into%20extended%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20it%20or%20not%2C%20the%20office%20provides%20social%20structure%2C%20and%20if%20you%20go%20too%20long%20without%20it%2C%20you%20may%20end%20up%20developing%20some%20overly%20unstructured%20behaviors.%20About%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20when%20I%20had%20a%20fully%20remote%20job%2C%20I'd%20go%20days%20without%20talking%20to%20other%20humans%20except%20for%20the%20ladies%20in%20my%20noon%20spin%20class%2C%20where%20I'm%20pretty%20sure%20I%20was%20the%20only%20person%20with%20a%20job.%20A%20while%20back%2C%20a%20friend%20of%20mine%20got%20into%20the%20habit%20of%20working%20from%20the%20tub%2C%20reading%20and%20typing%20away%20on%20the%20computer%20during%20hourlong%20baths.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EStrange%20habits%20at%20home%20don't%20stop%20at%20the%20front%20door.%20Remote%20work%20can%20also%20mean%20people%20get%20rusty%20on%20the%20softer%20skills%20needed%20around%20coworkers%20in%20the%20office.%20It%20may%20result%20in%20some%20awkwardness%2C%20whether%20perceived%20or%20real%2C%20when%20people%20are%20back%20at%20their%20desks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20the%20norms%20around%20formal%20communication%20have%20been%20maintained%20in%20remote%20and%20hybrid%20work.%20A%20meeting%20is%20a%20meeting%2C%20whether%20you're%20in%20a%20conference%20room%20or%20on%20Zoom.%20Messaging%20via%20email%20and%20Slack%20is%20the%20same.%20But%20informal%2C%20spontaneous%20communication%20%E2%80%94%20chatter%20on%20the%20walk%20to%20the%20meeting%2C%20an%20encounter%20at%20the%20watercooler%20or%20on%20the%20way%20to%20lunch%20%E2%80%94%20doesn't%20happen%20when%20people%20are%20remote.%20People's%20skills%20have%20shifted%20over%20time%20to%20match%20their%20environments.%20In%20a%20hybrid%20situation%2C%20perhaps%20some%20people's%20verbal-communication%20muscles%20got%20stronger%20but%20the%20nonverbal%20stuff%20got%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20environment%20doesn't%20lend%20itself%20to%20a%20normal%20interaction%2C%20all%20of%20these%20skill%20sets%20can%20become%20super%20challenging%20activities%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hakan%20Ozcelik%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20in%20the%20College%20of%20Business%20Administration%20at%20Sacramento%20State%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompounding%20the%20matter%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20don't%20get%20as%20much%20practice%20as%20they%20used%20to%20socializing%20in%20group%20settings%20outside%20of%20work.%20People%20are%20spending%20more%20time%20alone%3B%20they're%20not%20in%20church%20groups%20or%20book%20clubs%20or%20community%20organizations%20as%20they%20were%2C%20say%2C%2050%20years%20ago.%20So%20many%20of%20our%20modern%20interactions%20have%20moved%20online%20that%20it%20makes%20the%20in-real-life%20ones%20harder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20rules%20of%20engagement%20have%20gotten%20fuzzier%2C%20and%20that's%20what%20can%20trigger%20awkwardness%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Constance%20Noonan%20Hadley%2C%20an%20organizational%20psychologist%20who%20founded%20the%20Institute%20for%20Life%20at%20Work.%20Perhaps%20someone%20sees%20a%20group%20lunch%20at%20work%20and%2C%20because%20they%20haven't%20done%20something%20like%20that%20in%20so%20long%2C%20they're%20more%20nervous%20about%20joining%20than%20they%20would've%20been%20just%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECody%20Baertschi%2C%20a%20digital%20marketer%20who%20lives%20in%20Minnesota%2C%20feels%20like%20he's%20gotten%20the%20hang%20of%20virtual%20communication%20at%20work.%20He%20knows%20to%20talk%20to%20the%20Europeans%20about%20how%20cold%20it%20is%20there%20(in%20centigrade)%20and%20get%20down%20to%20business%20within%20the%20constructs%20of%20a%20video%20meeting.%20But%20for%20the%20normal%2C%20more%20%26quot%3Bold-school%20situations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20feels%20like%20he%20needs%20a%20manual.%20The%20small%20talk%20that%20takes%20place%20walking%20to%20and%20from%20a%20meeting%20is%20a%20struggle.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20the%20reps%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20not%20the%20construct%20of%20a%20call.%20There's%20not%20the%20comfort%20of%20being%20in%20your%20own%20space%20while%20having%20the%20conversations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20and%20his%20wife%20notice%20it%20when%20they%20meet%20other%20parents%20%E2%80%94%20they%20worry%20ahead%20of%20time%20about%20what%20to%20talk%20about.%20During%20the%20week%2C%20work%20can%20feel%20never-ending%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20hour%20of%20the%20day%20%E2%80%94%20a%20quality%20that's%20self-inflicted.%20It%20can%20also%20make%20him%20a%20little%20stir-crazy.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20weekend%20rolls%20around%2C%20it's%20like%20I've%20got%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20The%20Twin%20Cities%2C%20where%20he%20does%20his%20weekend-warrioring%2C%20are%20a%20two-hour%20drive%20away.%20But%20even%20the%20long%20time%20in%20the%20car%20is%20worth%20it%20to%20hit%20up%20the%20Mall%20of%20America%2C%20check%20out%20a%20museum%2C%20or%20do%20a%20hike.%20It's%20nice%20to%20go%20to%20restaurants%2C%20too%20%E2%80%94%20cooking%20his%20own%20lunch%20all%20week%20makes%20Baertschi%20eager%20to%20try%20someone%20else's%20cooking.%20%26quot%3BWho%20cares%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20out%20of%20the%20house.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%2C%20just%20as%20we%20can%20get%20worse%20at%20socializing%2C%20we%20can%20also%20get%20better.%20%26quot%3BSocial%20skills%20are%20truly%20a%20skill%2C%26quot%3B%20Noonan%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20something%20you%20can%20train.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20worth%20remembering%20that%20something%20you%20think%20is%20awkward%20might%20not%20be%20awkward%20to%20everyone%20else.%20A%20friend%20recently%20shared%20that%20she%20gets%20anxious%20that%20people%20can%20hear%20her%20walking%20in%20the%20office%20because%20of%20the%20click-clack%20of%20her%20shoes%2C%20which%20I%20would%20bet%20a%20million%20dollars%20is%20not%20a%20thing%20her%20coworkers%20are%20up%20in%20arms%20about%20(or%20have%20probably%20even%20noticed).%20Clearly%2C%20some%20WFH%20behaviors%20that%20are%20not%20appropriate%20for%20the%20office%3A%20Premeeting%20pump-up%20time%20blasting%20Katy%20Perry%20from%20your%20speakers%20at%20your%20desk%20is%20a%20no%2C%20as%20is%20wearing%20the%20same%20grimy%20sweatsuit%20for%20four%20days%20in%20a%20row.%20Behavior%20that's%20appropriate%20for%20the%20office%3A%20joining%20coworkers%20at%20the%20lunch%20table%20next%20to%20you%2C%20or%20stretching%20your%20legs%20with%20a%20midday%20walk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20as%20return-to-office%20mandates%20take%20hold%2C%20your%20coworkers%20might%20feel%20a%20little%20off%20about%20the%20whole%20thing%2C%20too.%20Maybe%20it'll%20give%20you%20something%20to%20talk%20about%20%E2%80%94%20or%20commiserate%20that%20you'd%20rather%20be%20home%2C%20doing%20your%20weird%20little%20habits%20in%20private.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-remote-work-weird-habits-return-to-office-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739869442000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67acb8e66630eb10385c5dcc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-remote-work-weird-habits-return-to-office-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22People%20are%20returning%20to%20the%20office%20%E2%80%94%20and%20after%20years%20of%20working%20from%20home%2C%20they've%20developed%20some%20weird%20new%20habits.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-remote-work-weird-habits-return-to-office-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20at%20CT%3A%20Batters%20blaze%2C%20bowlers%20charge%20in%20high-intensity%20sessions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739869395000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-118353073%2Cimgsize-44388.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Ficc-champions-trophy-2025%2Findia-at-champions-trophy-batters-blaze-bowlers-charge-in-high-intensity-sessions%2Farticleshow%2F118352870.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Indian%20cricket%20team%20has%20been%20intensively%20training%20at%20the%20ICC%20Academy%20in%20Dubai%20ahead%20of%20their%20matches%20against%20Bangladesh%20and%20Pakistan.%20Key%20players%20like%20Shubman%20Gill%2C%20Rishabh%20Pant%2C%20and%20Hardik%20Pandya%20showcased%20impressive%20performances%2C%20while%20bowlers%20like%20Mohammed%20Shami%20practiced%20extensively.%20The%20mood%20remained%20positive%20and%20upbeat%2C%20with%20both%20fun%20activities%20and%20serious%20preparations%20underway.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22SAHIL%20MALHOTRA%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump%20and%20Musk%20froze%20USAID%20funding%20to%20put%20Americans%20first.%20US%20citizens%20are%20feeling%20the%20impact.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20worker%20removes%20the%20U.S.%20Agency%20for%20International%20Development%20sign%20on%20their%20headquarters%20on%20February%207.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b392ceeb4be2fff9a4d637%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22661%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20worker%20removes%20the%20sign%20at%20the%20US%20Agency%20for%20International%20Development's%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20headquarters%20on%20February%207%2C%20after%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20Elon%20Musk%20abruptly%20froze%20the%20agency.%3Cp%3EKayla%20Bartkowski%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPresident%20Trump%20froze%20USAID%20spending%20to%20put%20%26quot%3BAmerican%20interests%26quot%3B%20first.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20decision%20has%20left%20at%20least%2012%2C700%20Americans%20jobless%2C%20a%20number%20that%20is%20expected%20to%20grow.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20North%20Carolina%2C%20home%20to%20some%20of%20the%20largest%20USAID%20contractors%2C%20hundreds%20have%20been%20furloughed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20have%20chosen%20to%20delay%20discretionary%20spending%20for%20new%20furniture%20and%20subscription%20services.%20They%20worry%20about%20being%20able%20to%20afford%20groceries%20for%20their%20families.%20And%20they%20have%20been%20left%20to%20wonder%20if%20they%20will%20get%20paid%20for%20work%20already%20performed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E's%20January%2020%20executive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalregister.gov%2Fdocuments%2F2025%2F01%2F30%2F2025-02091%2Freevaluating-and-realigning-united-states-foreign-aid%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorder%3C%2Fa%3E%20placed%20a%2090-day%20freeze%20on%20foreign%20aid%20in%20the%20name%20of%20putting%20%26quot%3BAmerican%20interests%26quot%3B%20first.%20That%20order%20and%20other%20actions%2C%20which%20halted%20work%20on%20hundreds%20of%20projects%20funded%20by%20the%20US%20Agency%20for%20International%20Development%2C%20known%20as%20USAID%2C%20have%20had%20profound%20ripple%20effects%20on%20American%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntended%20to%20reduce%20wasteful%20spending%20and%20limit%20the%20money%20the%20US%20sends%20overseas%2C%20the%20actions%20have%20impacted%20thousands%20of%20American%20workers%20whose%20jobs%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-musk-usaid-ukraine-middle-east-foreign-aid-aids-vaccinations-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efunded%20by%20USAID%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20funding%20freeze%20has%20been%20acutely%20felt%20in%20North%20Carolina%2C%20one%20of%20the%20top%20state%20recipients%20of%20USAID%20dollars%2C%20according%20to%20interviews%20with%20USAID%20contractors%20who%20have%20been%20furloughed%20or%20fired%20with%20little%20information%20about%20whether%20invoices%20for%20past%20work%20will%20be%20paid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20has%20implications%20for%20US%20farmers%2C%20furniture%20makers%2C%20airline%20carriers%2C%20and%20hundreds%20of%20other%20US%20organizations%20that%20sell%20products%20or%20services%20to%20the%20government%20agency.%20In%20fact%2C%20USAID%20rules%20require%20a%20range%20of%20purchases%20%E2%80%94%20from%20food%20to%20vehicles%20to%20pharmaceuticals%20and%20plane%20tickets%20%E2%80%94%20to%20prioritize%20US%20vendors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BForeign%20aid%2C%20with%20a%20few%20exceptions%20for%20close%20allies%20such%20as%20Egypt%2C%20Israel%2C%20and%20Jordan%2C%20is%20not%20transferred%20into%20the%20treasuries%20of%20aid%20recipient%20governments%2C%26quot%3B%20Andrew%20Natsios%2C%20a%20former%20administrator%20of%20USAID%2C%20said%20in%20February%2013%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2F119%2Fmeeting%2Fhouse%2F117889%2Fwitnesses%2FHHRG-119-FA00-Wstate-NatsiosA-20250213.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etestimony%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20Congress.%20%26quot%3BInstead%2C%20it%20is%20spent%20through%20international%20and%20local%20non-governmental%20organizations%2C%20US%20and%20local%20universities%2C%20for-profit%20development%20contractors%2C%20and%20civil%20society%20organizations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20now%2C%20USAID%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fusaid-staff-put-on-administrative-leave-friday-midnight-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emaintained%20a%20staff%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20around%2010%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Congressional%20Research%20Service%2C%20relying%20on%20contractors%20to%20do%20the%20bulk%20of%20its%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20administration's%20decision%20to%20defund%20USAID%20%E2%80%94%20Elon%20Musk%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Felonmusk%2Fstatus%2F1886307316804263979%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20this%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20%26quot%3Bspent%20the%20weekend%20feeding%20USAID%20into%20the%20wood%20chipper%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20has%20led%20to%20the%20layoff%20or%20termination%20of%20thousands%20of%20US%20employees%20at%20companies%20that%20contract%20with%20USAID%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usaidstopwork.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUSAID%20tracker%3C%2Fa%3E%20set%20up%20by%20Molloy%20Consultants%2C%20a%20global%20health%20consulting%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20and%20the%20State%20Department%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20about%20the%20impact%20on%20US%20workers.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20trying%20to%20be%20disruptive%20to%20people's%20personal%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Marco%20Rubio%20said%20on%20February%207.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20being%20punitive%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPete%20Marocco%2C%20deputy%20administrator%20for%20USAID%2C%20said%20in%20a%20February%2010%20affidavit%20that%20the%20pause%20was%20necessary%20in%20order%20to%20enable%20%26quot%3Ba%20thorough%20review%20of%20USAID's%20operations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222719a9fc-497c-4039-ad8b-29fce2363b50%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENorth%20Carolina%20takes%20a%20hit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20impact%20of%20the%20funding%20freeze%20was%20immediate%20in%20North%20Carolina%2C%20one%20of%20the%20top%20state%20recipients%20of%20USAID%20dollars.%20The%20state%20is%20home%20to%20organizations%20that%20received%20more%20than%20%242.2%20billion%20from%20USAID%2C%20according%20to%20Molloy%20Consultants%2C%20placing%20it%20fifth%20among%20US%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20will%20be%20very%20blunt.%20The%20freeze%20has%20been%20devastating%2C%26quot%3B%20Brianna%20Clarke-Schwelm%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20North%20Carolina%20Global%20Health%20Alliance%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAlready%20we%20are%20seeing%20mass%20furloughs%20and%20mass%20layoffs.%20Hundreds%20of%20people%20have%20already%20lost%20their%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20impact%20%26quot%3Bwill%20reach%20people%20in%20every%20corner%20of%20our%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENorth%20Carolina%20is%20Trump%20country%3B%20the%20president%20won%20the%20state%20in%202016%2C%202020%2C%20and%202024%2C%20and%20he%20visited%20it%20at%20least%2011%20times%20during%20last%20year's%20campaign%2C%20more%20than%20almost%20any%20other%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESenators%20Thom%20Tillis%20and%20Ted%20Budd%2C%20both%20Republicans%2C%20didn't%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%20Both%20senators%20have%20fielded%20calls%20and%20emails%20from%20constituents%2C%20often%20responding%20with%20impersonal%20emails%2C%20according%20to%20some%20recipients%20who%20spoke%20to%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20government%20has%20a%20responsibility%20to%20review%20every%20taxpayer%20dollar%20and%20ensure%20that%20it%20is%20spent%20wisely%20and%20in%20the%20best%20interest%20of%20the%20American%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20Budd's%20emails%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentative%20Valerie%20Foushee%2C%20a%20Democrat%20whose%20district%20includes%20Durham%2C%20said%20she%20had%20heard%20from%20hundreds%20of%20constituents%20concerned%20about%20the%20funding%20freeze.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20deeply%20concerned%20regarding%20the%20illegal%20actions%20taken%20by%20the%20Trump%20Administration%20to%20dismantle%20our%20leading%20foreign%20aid%20agency%2C%26quot%3B%20Foushee%20said%20by%20email.%20%26quot%3BTrump's%20detrimental%20Stop%20Work%20Order%20will%20have%20widespread%20repercussions%20across%20our%20state%2C%20affecting%20farmers%2C%20local%20businesses%2C%20researchers%2C%20medical%20professionals%2C%20biotech%20companies%2C%20and%20many%20others.%20In%20my%20district%20alone%2C%20thousands%20of%20workers%20across%20numerous%20international%20development%20organizations%20will%20be%20affected.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENorth%20Carolina's%20Raleigh-Durham%20metro%20area%20is%20home%20to%20two%20of%20the%20six%20largest%20global%20recipients%20of%20USAID%20funds%20between%202013%20and%202022%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrsreports.congress.gov%2Fproduct%2Fpdf%2FR%2FR48150%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Congressional%20Research%20Service.%20FHI%20360%2C%20a%20Durham-based%20nonprofit%20focused%20on%20health%2C%20nutrition%2C%20and%20economic%20opportunity%2C%20received%20%243.79%20billion%20during%20those%20years%20and%20RTI%20International%2C%20a%20research%20institution%20based%20in%20Research%20Triangle%20Park%2C%20took%20in%20%242.31%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20February%206%2C%20FHI%20360%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fhi360.org%2Fnews%2Ffhi-360-announces-u-s-staff-furloughs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20would%20furlough%2036%25%20of%20its%20US%20staff%2C%20including%20200%20in%20North%20Carolina.%20Spokesperson%20Jennifer%20Garcia%20declined%20to%20elaborate%20on%20the%20announcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20week%20later%2C%20RTI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rti.org%2Fnews%2Frti-international-announces-temporary-staff-layoffs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisclosed%3C%2Fa%3E%20temporary%20layoffs%20for%20226%20of%20its%20staff%2C%20including%2061%20in%20North%20Carolina.%20%26quot%3BRTI%20deeply%20values%20every%20staff%20member%2C%26quot%3B%20CEO%20Tim%20Gabel%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20%26quot%3BThe%20projects%20our%20international%20development%20staff%20implement%20provide%20essential%20contributions%20that%20support%20America's%20leadership%20in%20creating%20a%20more%20prosperous%2C%20safe%2C%20secure%20and%20resilient%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20others%20among%20the%20top%20organizations%20receiving%20USAID%20funds%2C%20Chemonics%20and%20DAI%2C%20also%20employ%20workers%20in%20the%20state.%20Chemonics%20has%20furloughed%20600%20staff%20and%20placed%20another%20300%20on%20limited%20work%20hours%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2025%2F02%2F04%2Fpolitics%2Fusaid-cuts-thousands-american-jobs%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20spokesperson%20told%20CNN%3C%2Fa%3E.%20DAI%20furloughed%20about%20380%20staff%2C%2060%20to%2070%25%20of%20their%20workforce%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20told%20the%20network.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20Monday%2C%20at%20least%2012%2C700%20contractors%20who%20relied%20on%20USAID%20funding%20had%20been%20furloughed%20or%20put%20on%20leave%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usaidstopwork.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enumbers%20compiled%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Molloy%20Consultants%20from%20impacted%20organizations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20global%20health%20industry%20is%20a%20significant%20driver%20of%20North%20Carolina's%20economy.%20The%20industry%20accounted%20for%20roughly%20170%2C000%20jobs%20in%20the%20state%20and%20added%20almost%20%2432%20billion%20in%20value%20to%20the%20state's%20economy%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncglobalhealth.org%2F_files%2Fugd%2F6acda1_0544a60a3d3643a1b789e8d1a0206495.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20commissioned%20by%20NCGHA.%20That's%20about%204%25%20of%20the%20state's%20GDP%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20who%20have%20lost%20their%20jobs%20or%20been%20furloughed%2C%20the%20last%20few%20weeks%20have%20been%20traumatic.%20Many%20told%20BI%20they%20are%20applying%20for%20unemployment%20benefits.%20One%20person%20decided%20to%20cancel%20plans%20to%20buy%20a%20new%20North%20Carolina-made%20couch%20after%20being%20put%20on%20furlough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20folks%20realize%20how%20big%20of%20an%20industry%20this%20is%20for%20America%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20person%20who%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20named%20to%20avoid%20professional%20repercussions.%20%26quot%3BJust%20in%20the%20Triangle%20you%20have%20two%20of%20the%20largest%20implementers%20in%20the%20world%2C%20and%20then%20countless%20NGOs%20impacted.%20Multiply%20that%20by%2049%20states.%20How%20many%20jobs%20are%20we%20talking%20about%20here%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20April%2C%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%20said%20it%20would%20spend%20%241%20billion%20to%20buy%20US%20commodities%20for%20USAID%20to%20ship%20overseas.%20A%20USAID%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic1.squarespace.com%2Fstatic%2F679bdd21823c9474a907e5b3%2Ft%2F67aa49892462b91f2c032559%2F1739213201516%2FNorth%2BCarolina%2BUSAID.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efact%20sheet%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20the%20agency%20partnered%20with%20at%20least%2027%20North%20Carolina%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmall%20businesses%20have%20also%20been%20impacted.%20In%20December%2C%20a%20government%20official%20said%20the%20agency%20sent%20%241%20billion%20to%20US%20small%20businesses%20in%20the%20last%20fiscal%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESupport%20for%20small%20firms%20has%20included%20State%20Department%20purchases%20of%20at%20least%20%247.5%20million%20furniture%20over%20the%20last%20eight%20years%20from%20North%20Carolina%20manufacturers%20to%20fill%20embassies%2C%20missions%2C%20residences%2C%20and%20USAID%20facilities%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usaspending.gov%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eusaspending.gov%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20this%20continues%2C%2090%25%20of%20the%20NGO%20and%20contractor%20community%20will%20cease%20to%20exist%20within%20another%20month%2C%26quot%3B%20Natsio%20said%20in%20his%20testimony%20last%20week.%20%26quot%3BNGOs%2C%20many%20of%20them%20faith-based%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fevangelical-leaders-respond-donald-trump-usaid-foreign-aid-cuts-doge-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChristian%20organizations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20will%20be%20forced%20to%20shut%20down%20programs%2C%20lay%20off%20staff%20(which%20many%20have%20already%20been%20forced%20to%20do)%2C%20and%20ultimately%20close%20their%20doors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20USAID%20spending%20freeze%20has%20also%20affected%20the%20state's%20universities%2C%20as%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%20system%2C%20North%20Carolina%20State%20University%2C%20North%20Carolina%20A%26amp%3BT%20State%20University%2C%20and%20Duke%20University%20had%20all%20received%20USAID%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%20at%20Chapel%20Hill's%20Carolina%20Population%20Center%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cpc.unc.edu%2Fnews%2Func-awarded-90-million-global-health-pearl-project-to-support-localized-generation-and-use-of-evidence-and-data%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereceived%20a%20%2490%20million%20grant%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20USAID%20to%20monitor%20global%20health.%20Between%202003%20and%202015%2C%20the%20center's%20Measure%20Evaluation%20program%20received%20an%20additional%20%24500%20million%20from%20USAID%20to%20handle%20data%20collection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUNC%20Chapel%20Hill%20has%2010%20stop%20work%20orders%20from%20USAID%2C%20including%20three%20in%20which%20the%20university%20is%20a%20direct%20recipient%20and%20another%20seven%20in%20which%20it%20is%20a%20subrecipient%2C%20spokesperson%20Cat%20Long%20said%20by%20email.%20The%20university%20had%20received%20%2418.3%20million%20in%20research%20awards%20this%20fiscal%20year%20and%20%2417.5%20million%20in%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20University%20is%20awaiting%20more%20information%20from%20federal%20agencies%20to%20determine%20the%20long-term%20impact%20on%20these%20programs%20and%20their%20staff%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%E2%80%AF%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENC%20State%20%26quot%3Bis%20working%20with%20various%20partners%20to%20gauge%20potential%20impacts%20of%20any%20changes%20to%20federally%20funded%20sponsored%20programs%2C%26quot%3B%20university%20spokesperson%20Mick%20Kulikowski%20said%20by%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChemonics%2C%20DAI%2C%20and%20the%20Small%20Business%20Association%20for%20International%20Companies%2C%20a%20Raleigh-based%20trade%20association%20with%20more%20than%20150%20members%2C%20were%20among%20eight%20plaintiffs%20who%20filed%20suit%20on%20February%2011%20to%20challenge%20the%20administration's%20freeze.%20Two%20days%20later%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20issued%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-musk-doge-usaid-shutdown-blocked-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etemporary%20restraining%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20giving%20the%20administration%20five%20days%20to%20restart%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOrganizations%20representing%20USAID%20workers%20have%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fusaid-employment-cut-foreign-aid-trump-rubio-lawsuit-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiled%20suit%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20uncertainty%20reigns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20senior%20staff%20member%20at%20one%20of%20the%20major%20North%20Carolina%20organizations%20funded%20by%20USAID%20said%20organizations%20still%20don't%20know%20if%20invoices%20for%20work%20performed%20in%20November%2C%20December%2C%20and%20January%20will%20be%20paid.%20Another%20said%20that%20organizations%20are%20furloughing%20staff%20simply%20because%20they%20don't%20have%20any%20cash%20on%20hand%20to%20pay%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultiple%20furloughed%20employees%20of%20USAID%20contractors%20said%20that%20their%20projects%20are%20heavily%20audited%2C%20and%20they%20pushed%20back%20on%20the%20idea%20that%20there%20is%20widespread%20wasteful%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20one%20of%20the%20most%20successfully%20audited%20organizations%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20person%20who'd%20been%20furloughed.%20%26quot%3BMonitoring%20and%20evaluation%20is%20such%20a%20big%20part%20of%20every%20project.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you%20work%20for%20USAID%2C%20a%20USAID%20contractor%2C%20or%20another%20government%20agency%20affected%20by%20furloughs%2C%20please%20contact%20Dakin%20Campbell%20at%20dcampbell%40insider.com%20or%20text%20him%20securely%20at%20dakin.11%20on%20the%20Signal%20app.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-elon-musk-usaid-funding-freeze-layoffs-furloughs-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739869322000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b39464eb4be2fff9a4d645%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-elon-musk-usaid-funding-freeze-layoffs-furloughs-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Trump%20administration%20shut%20down%20USAID%20to%20put%20'American%20interests'%20first.%20In%20North%20Carolina%2C%20the%20freeze%20has%20thrown%20hundreds%20out%20of%20work.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dcampbell%2Bweb%40insider.com%20(Dakin%20Campbell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-elon-musk-usaid-funding-freeze-layoffs-furloughs-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20boomer%20made%20%2447%2C000%20last%20year%20from%20his%20remote%20side%20hustle%20answering%20questions%20about%20art%20and%20antiques%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22545%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22David%20C.%20Bond%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ae32d76630eb10385c8e93%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22409%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDavid%20C.%20Bond%20made%20%2447%2C000%20last%20year%20answering%20questions%20about%20art%20and%20antiques%20on%20JustAnswer.%3Cp%3EDavid%20C.%20Bond%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDavid%20C.%20Bond%20earned%20%2447%2C000%20last%20year%20answering%20questions%20about%20art%20on%20the%20platform%20JustAnswer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20gets%20paid%20between%20%247.50%20and%20%2411.50%20per%20question%20and%20aims%20to%20answer%20about%2020%20per%20day.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFreelance%20gigs%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-started-on-justanswer-an-antiques-appraisal-site-2023-9%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJustAnswer%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20become%20popular%20as%20people%20look%20for%20additional%20income.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20David%20C.%20Bond%20develops%20a%20longer-term%20career%20project%2C%20he's%20doing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-started-on-justanswer-an-antiques-appraisal-site-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egig%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20taps%20his%20expertise%20in%20art.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20early%202023%2C%20Bond%20has%20worked%20for%20JustAnswer%2C%20a%20platform%20that%20connects%20users%20with%20questions%20to%20experts%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewho%20can%20try%20to%20help.%20Many%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A