ashington%20Post%20scrapped%20an%20ad%20calling%20for%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20to%20%26quot%3Bfire%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20that%20was%20slated%20to%20run%20in%20some%20of%20its%20Tuesday%20print%20editions%2C%20according%20to%20one%20of%20the%20organizations%20that%20ordered%20the%20ad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdvocacy%20group%20Common%20Cause%20had%20agreed%20to%20pay%20%24115%2C000%20to%20the%20Post%20to%20run%20an%20ad%20criticizing%20billionaire%20Elon%20Musk%20wrapped%20around%20the%20newspapers%20and%20a%20similar%20ad%20inside%20the%20paper%2C%20the%20organization%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ads%20are%20part%20of%20a%20bigger%20campaign%20by%20Common%20Cause%20called%20%26quot%3BFire%20Elon%20Musk%2C%26quot%3B%20urging%20people%20to%20sign%20a%20petition%20calling%20for%20Musk's%20removal%20as%20the%20head%20of%20the%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-department-of-government-efficiency%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ad%2C%20which%20Common%20Cause%20later%20posted%20on%20its%20website%2C%20features%20Elon%20Musk%20laughing%20behind%20an%20image%20of%20the%20White%20House%2C%20and%20says%20in%20large%20text%2C%20%26quot%3BWho's%20running%20this%20country%3A%20Donald%20Trump%20or%20Elon%20Musk%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmaller%20text%20below%20the%20image%20states%20that%20the%20Tesla%20CEO%20%26quot%3Bhas%20created%20chaos%20and%20confusion%20and%20put%20our%20livelihoods%20at%20risk%26quot%3B%20and%20notes%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Constitution%20only%20allows%20for%20one%20president%20at%20a%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20said%20the%20Post%20initially%20approved%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20ad%20but%20that%20the%20Post%20informed%20Common%20Cause%20on%20Friday%20of%20its%20decision%20to%20drop%20the%20wrap%20ad%20from%20publication%20without%20explanation.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Post%20said%20it%20would%20allow%20Common%20Cause%20to%20run%20its%20similar%20ad%20inside%20the%20paper%2C%20per%20the%20organization%2C%20but%20Common%20Cause%20declined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20deeply%20concerning%20that%20our%20ad%20was%20censored%20and%20rejected%20without%20a%20valid%20reason%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Virginia%20Kase%20Solom%C3%B3n%2C%20Common%20Cause's%20president%20and%20CEO%2C%20and%20Margaret%20Huang%2C%20Southern%20Poverty%20Law%20Center's%20president%20and%20CEO%2C%20in%20a%20joint%20statement.%20Common%20Cause%20planned%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20ads%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20Southern%20Poverty%20Law%20Center%20Action%20Fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20this%20is%20limiting%20our%20freedom%20of%20expression%20at%20a%20critical%20time%20in%20our%20nation's%20history.%20This%20seems%20to%20show%20the%20Washington%20Post%20is%20feeling%20pressure%20to%20cover%20the%20news%20a%20certain%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Kase%20Solom%C3%B3n%20and%20Huang%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Post%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20its%20internal%20decisions%20about%20advertising%20campaigns.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fwp-stat%2Fsite%2Fmediakit%2Fmediakit-ad-policy.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvertising%20guidelines%3C%2Fa%3E%20state%20that%20the%20Post%20%26quot%3Baccepts%20all%20types%20of%20advertising%20and%20does%20not%20decline%20advertising%20unless%20there%20is%20a%20compelling%20reason%20to%20do%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20%26quot%3Bnonetheless%20reserves%20the%20right%20to%20position%2C%20revise%2C%20or%20refuse%20to%20publish%20any%20advertisement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ads%20are%20part%20of%20a%20bigger%20campaign%20by%20Common%20Cause%20called%20%26quot%3BFire%20Elon%20Musk%2C%26quot%3B%20urging%20people%20to%20sign%20a%20petition%20calling%20fo