ajoring%20in%20finance%20and%20working%20with%20stocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20ideas%20sounded%20great%20for%20a%20little%20while%2C%20but%20I%20can't%20stop%20thinking%20about%20this%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20with%20a%20twinkle%20in%20his%20eyes.%20He's%20been%20mentioning%20this%20on%20and%20off%20for%20some%20time%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-office-fun-facts-2018-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eafter%20watching%20%26quot%3BThe%20Office%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20favorite%20show%20of%20mine%20and%20my%20husband%20that%20I%20reluctantly%20let%20him%20watch%20despite%20the%20crude%20humor%20%E2%80%94%20he%20was%20sure%20this%20is%20what%20he%20was%20meant%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20who%20am%20I%20to%20tell%20him%20he%20can't%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225f3bd54b-3966-4073-9331-1a0dc00b8af7%5C%22%3EI'm%20giving%20my%20kids%20different%20career%20advice%20than%20what%20I%20got%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20talked%20about%20his%20aspirations%2C%20he%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20think%20I%20have%20what%20it%20takes%3F%26quot%3B%20Suddenly%2C%20I%20heard%20the%20voices%20of%20every%20adult%20from%20my%20childhood%3A%20%26quot%3BWriting%20is%20a%20hobby%2C%20not%20a%20career.%20It%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-get-medical-bills-reduced-negotiate-challenge-payment-plan-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewon't%20pay%20the%20bills%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20told%20him%20he%20was%20very%20creative%20and%20believed%20he%20had%20what%20it%20took%20to%20succeed.%20That%20was%20the%20truth.%20But%20there%20was%20more%20to%20my%20answer%20than%20simply%20persuading%20him%20to%20put%20all%20his%20efforts%20into%20that%20one%20dream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20came%20time%20for%20me%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhelping-my-son-through-college-application-process-tours-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapply%20to%20college%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20my%20parents%20gave%20me%20two%20pieces%20of%20advice%3A%20Choose%20a%20career%20that%20pays%20enough%20for%20you%20to%20support%20yourself%20AND%20one%20that%20will%20always%20have%20job%20vacancies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20constructive%20guidance%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I'll%20pass%20this%20wisdom%20on%20to%20my%20own%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20but%20perhaps%20they%20missed%20one%20small%20detail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20I%20knew%20that%20English%20and%20science%20were%20the%20two%20subjects%20I%20was%20most%20interested%20in.%20I%20also%20enjoyed%20working%20with%20children%2C%20and%20the%20idea%20of%20working%20in%20a%20school%20appealed%20to%20me.%20So%2C%20when%20my%20mother%20suggested%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspeech-therapy-helped-my-toddler-throw-fewer-fits-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espeech-language%20pathology%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20potential%20career%2C%20it%20seemed%20like%20the%20perfect%20fit.%20There%20was%20a%20surge%20in%20jobs%20for%20speech-language%20pathologists%20(SLPs)%20in%202001%2C%20when%20I%20began%20college%20and%20enrolled%20in%20the%20course%20that%20introduced%20the%20major.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20writing%2C%20but%20no%20one%20said%20to%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BChoose%20the%20job%20you%20can't%20live%20without.%26quot%3B%20%3Cem%3EThat%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20the%20advice%20I%20never%20got.%20And%20so%2C%20I%20let%20writing%20slip%20away%20into%20the%20dust%20of%20my%20childhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223f4af478-74be-4fb0-969c-bcf113dd2397%5C%22%3EI%20had%20to%20parent%20while%20living%20with%20a%20chronic%20illness%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-a-degree-while-working-full-time-job-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearning%20my%20master's%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20worked%20in%20the%20field%20as%20an%20SLP%20in%20an%20elementary%20school%20for%20a%20few%20years%20until%20my%20son%20was%20born.%20It%20wasn't%20hard%20to%20say%20bye%20to%20an%20over-filled%20caseload%20and%20endless%20paperwork%2C%20but%20I%20did%20eventually%20miss%20feeling%20like%20a%20professional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20khakis%20and%20a%20blouse%2C%20I%20wore%20pajamas%20or%20leggings%20on%20a%20good%20day.%20I%20was%20Mom%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20woman%20searching%20for%20a%20diagnosis%20that%20I%20eventually%20discovered%20was%20multiple%20sclerosis%20%E2%80%94%20and%20life%20was%20now%20filled%20with%20many%20firsts%2C%20both%20wonderful%20motherly%20firsts%2C%20and%20frightening%20disease-worsening%20firsts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20intended%20to%20go%20back%20to%20work%20when%20my%20younger%20son%20was%20in%20full-day%20school%2C%20but%20between%20mothering%20and%20living%20with%20a%20chronic%20illness%2C%20my%20inner%20creativity%20won.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2263b96041-386c-4448-be74-3250551dff0f%5C%22%3EI%20started%20writing%20again%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20slowly.%20At%20first%2C%20I%20simply%20wanted%20to%20connect%20with%20others%20who%20were%20also%20living%20with%20an%20undiagnosed%20disease.%20When%20I%20finally%20received%20my%20diagnosis%2C%20I%20then%20hoped%20to%20be%20an%20advocate%20for%20those%20who%20remained%20undiagnosed%20as%20well%20as%20the%20MS%20community%2C%20so%20I%20continued%20writing%20with%20these%20goals%20in%20mind.%20But%2C%20later%2C%20as%20my%20publications%20widened%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20branch%20out%20%E2%80%94%20to%20write%20about%20parenting%2C%20politics%20that%20impacted%20my%20family's%20life%2C%20and%20what%20I%20thought%20about%20the%20recent%20episode%20of%20my%20favorite%20TV%20show.%20I%20wanted%20to%20write%20it%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20a%20degree%20in%20journalism%2C%20I%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20homework%20to%20do.%20I%20joined%20writer's%20groups%20on%20social%20media%20and%20read%20about%20how%20to%20send%20editors%20pitches%20that%20get%20noticed.%20Over%20time%2C%20I%20became%20accustomed%20to%20radio%20silence%20and%20rejections%20from%20editors.%20A%20lot%20of%20behind-the-scenes%20research%20eventually%20enabled%20me%20to%20get%20my%20foot%20in%20the%20door.%20But%20it%20wasn't%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20whim%2C%20I%20emailed%20an%20editor%20at%20a%20publication%20I%20aspired%20to%20see%20my%20name%20in.%20Like%20any%20enthusiastic%20creator%20with%20a%20goal%2C%20I%20sent%20a%20draft%20of%20an%20essay%20I'd%20been%20working%20on.%20It%20was%20rejected.%20All%20in%20the%20same%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20later%20I%20landed%20my%20first%20essay%20in%20that%20publication.%20Often%2C%20I%20wonder%20how%20I%20found%20success%20in%20an%20industry%20that%20so%20few%20make%20it%20in.%20Then%20I%20remember%20writing%20gives%20me%20the%20twinkle%20I%20see%20in%20my%20son's%20eyes%20when%20he%20talks%20about%20screenwriting%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20why%20I%20believe%20he%20also%20has%20what%20it%20takes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225efb7e18-6d8e-42f9-8e3a-a3ca03c43ea2%5C%22%3EI'm%20thankful%20I%20have%20a%20degree%20to%20fall%20back%20on%20if%20needed%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20gave%20me%20good%20advice%20before%20I%20left%20for%20college.%20I'm%20not%20breaking%20the%20bank%20as%20a%20freelance%20writer.%20But%2C%20because%20of%20their%20guidance%2C%20I%20have%20a%20degree%20to%20fall%20back%20on%20should%20I%20need%20it%2C%20and%20I'll%20never%20regret%20having%20that%20safety%20net.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20believe%20there's%20more%20to%20convey%20to%20children%20than%20choosing%20a%20career%20solely%20based%20on%20pay%20and%20job%20availability.%20Like%20any%20parent%2C%20I%20want%20my%20children%20to%20live%20comfortably%20and%20with%20job%20security%2C%20but%20I%20also%20want%20them%20to%20pursue%20the%20career%20they%20can't%20live%20without%20%E2%80%94%20because%20that's%20what%20life%20is%20all%20about.%20If%20my%20children's%20eyes%20light%20up%20when